    "description": "A security-response lane (the core security response process, security advisory publication, CVE/GHSA publication, emergency disable capability, or mirror/offline publication drills) carries a Stable (or LTS) readiness promise only when its response packet is within its freshness SLO, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, every required emergency control is satisfied and every required mirror drill checkpoint is verified, an owner has signed off, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A lane that loses any of those carries a label below the cutline (beta, preview, withdrawn) and never inherits an adjacent lane's ready label."
  },
  "release_blocking_lane_refs": [
    "lane:security_response_process",
    "lane:advisory_publication",
